SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 964
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Pope's Garden Center
on the occasion of its fiftieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing
those exemplary businesses that, through an abiding commitment to excellence, have
contributed greatly to this State for many years; and
WHEREAS, Pope's Garden Center is one such esteemed enterprise, which celebrated
its fiftieth anniversary in 2025, a commendable milestone for this family-owned, independently
run business; and
WHEREAS, founded in 1975 by Robert "Bubba" Pope, Pope's Garden Center began as
a modest operation focused on growing and selling vegetable plants, with its roots in the
wholesale market and a dedication to quality horticulture; and
WHEREAS, through perseverance and entrepreneurial spirit, the business expanded
from its early beginnings to include greenhouse operations and retail garden centers,
establishing a strong presence in the Knoxville and Maryville areas; and
WHEREAS, over the decades, Pope's Garden Center has remained a family-owned and
-operated business, with three generations of the Pope family contributing to its continued
success and upholding its founding values of hard work, integrity, and customer service; and
WHEREAS, today, Pope's Garden Center operates multiple garden centers and plant
farms in East Tennessee, including locations in Maryville, Greenback, and Knoxville, while
continuing to serve both retail customers and wholesale partners; and
WHEREAS, the business has demonstrated a remarkable ability to adapt to changing
market conditions, evolving from a primarily wholesale operation to a thriving retail presence
while maintaining its commitment to locally grown products and personalized service; and
SJR0964
016237
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Pope's Garden Center has played an important role in the local economy by
providing employment opportunities and supporting the agricultural and horticultural traditions of
the region; and
WHEREAS, deeply rooted in their community, the Pope family and their employees take
pride in serving their neighbors and contributing to the quality of life in East Tennessee through
their dedication to excellence in gardening and plant cultivation; and
WHEREAS, for fifty years, Pope's Garden Center has exemplified what it means to be a
family-run business, standing as a testament to the enduring strength of family enterprise and
the value of commitment to one's community; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Pope's Garden Center
upon the celebration of its fiftieth anniversary and extend to its owners and employees our best
wishes for many more years of continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
